## Key Trait: EmbeddingProvider

This is the central abstraction for all AI embedding work. **All new AI providers
must implement this trait.** Do not bypass it by calling HTTP clients or model APIs
directly from business logic.

```rust
use crate::embeddings::EmbeddingModelInfo;

#[async_trait]
pub trait EmbeddingProvider: Send + Sync {
    async fn embed(&self, text: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>>;
    async fn embed_batch(&self, texts: Vec<String>) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>>;
    fn dimensions(&self) -> Result<usize>;
    fn max_tokens(&self) -> Result<usize>;
    fn provider_type(&self) -> EmbeddingProviderType;
    /// Returns our own EmbeddingModelInfo type — NOT fastembed's ModelInfo.
    fn model_info(&self) -> Option<EmbeddingModelInfo>;
}
```

**Current implementations:**
- `LemonadeProvider` — HTTP to Lemonade Server (`POST /api/v1/embeddings`). The only
  active implementation. FastEmbed/ONNX have been removed.

**Pattern for adding a new HTTP-based provider:**
```rust
pub struct MyProvider {
    client: reqwest::Client,
    base_url: String,
    model: String,
    dimensions: usize,  // probe on construction
}

#[async_trait]
impl EmbeddingProvider for MyProvider {
    async fn embed(&self, text: &str) -> Result<Vec<f32>> {
        let resp: serde_json::Value = self.client
            .post(format!("{}/embeddings", self.base_url))
            .header("Authorization", "Bearer token")
            .json(&serde_json::json!({ "model": self.model, "input": [text] }))
            .send().await?
            .json().await?;
        let embedding = resp["data"][0]["embedding"]
            .as_array()
            .ok_or_else(|| anyhow!("No embedding in response"))?
            .iter()
            .map(|v| v.as_f64().unwrap_or(0.0) as f32)
            .collect();
        Ok(embedding)
    }

    fn model_info(&self) -> Option<EmbeddingModelInfo> {
        Some(EmbeddingModelInfo {
            name: self.model.clone(),
            dimensions: self.dimensions,
            description: None,
        })
    }
    // ... other methods
}
```

