## String-Based Edge Types

Always use descriptive string literals for relationships. The deprecated enum
variants (`Contains`, `OwnedBy`, `LocatedIn`, `MemberOf`) exist only for backward
compatibility — never use them in new code.

```rust
// Correct
graph.connect_objects_str(character_id, location_id, "located_in")?;
graph.connect_objects_str(faction_id, territory_id, "controls")?;
graph.connect_objects_str(npc_id, quest_id, "offers")?;
graph.connect_objects_weighted_str(sauron_id, frodo_id, "enemy_of", 0.9)?;
```

